name: pingue
note: The -gaster ending is masculine, so if the species epithet is an adjective, then it should be pinguis. 'pingue' would be the neuter form. However, if the species epithet is a noun in apposition (The grease Thaxterogaster) then pingue is correct; 'greasy' is an adjective, 'grease' is the noun
